article.description: — Trae Benham had a season-high 26 points as Lipscomb defeated Central Arkansas 81-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Benham carries Lipscomb past Cent. Arkansas 81-66
article.linkText: Benham carries Lipscomb past Cent. Arkansas 81-66
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- — Trae Benham had a season-high 26 points as Lipscomb defeated Central Arkansas 81-66 on Saturday. Ahsan Asadullah had 15 points, 10 rebounds, six assists and four blocks for Lipscomb (13-18, 6-10 Atlantic Sun Conference). Greg Jones added 10 points. KJ Johnson had 10 points and six rebounds. Eddy Kayouloud had 22 points and three blocks for the Bears (10-19, 7-9). Darious Hall added 11 points and nine rebounds. The Bisons evened the season series against the Bears. Central Arkansas defeated Lipscomb 93-88 on Jan. 9. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
